The paper proposes a novel approach for automatic sleep staging using a hierarchical recurrent neural network. The network architecture involves filterbank and attention-based recurrent layers for epoch processing and a recurrent layer for sequence processing. The paper also presents an end-to-end training strategy and achieves state-of-the-art results on a publicly available dataset. Given these details, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.CL (Computation and Language).
